According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Adaptive Traffic Signal Control System Market was valued at USD 1,507 million in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 2,869 million by 2034, growing at a CAGR of 9.7% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing significant momentum as governments and transportation authorities increasingly invest in intelligent traffic management solutions to reduce congestion, improve road safety, and support sustainable urban development. The rapid expansion of smart city initiatives, coupled with advancements in artificial intelligence (AI), Internet of Things (IoT), and cloud-based traffic management technologies, is driving widespread adoption of adaptive traffic signal control systems across developed and emerging economies.
